  "texts": [
    "Methods, doi: 10.3758/s13428-024-02441-0 (2024).",
    "In all studies, we used LLMs to filter participants who did not supply a genuine conspiracy theory.",
    "Specifically, we used GPT-4 Turbo to evaluate each participant's free-response conspiracy statement using three prompts, which are provided in Table S4 (model temperature = 0).",
    "Prompt 1 was applied to both participants' raw, open-ended text responses describing their focal conspiracy and, in a separate model call, to the GPT-summarized conspiracy statements.",
    "Prompt 2, which was intended to determine whether the statement contained a conspiracy theory (ignoring whether the statement described belief in a conspiracy), was applied only to the GPTsummarized conspiracy statements."
  ],
